.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH handle 1  "handle " 
.SH NAME
handle \- Accept or dismiss the current browser dialog
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBhandle\fR [\fB\-\-text\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIACTION\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Accept or dismiss the currently open browser dialog (alert, confirm, prompt, or beforeunload). A dialog must be open before this command can be used. For prompt dialogs, use \-\-text to provide the response text when accepting.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-text\fR \fI<TEXT>\fR
Response text for prompt dialogs (only used with \*(Aqaccept\*(Aq action)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIACTION\fR>
Action to take: accept or dismiss
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
accept: Accept (OK) the dialog
.IP \(bu 2
dismiss: Dismiss (Cancel) the dialog
.RE
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  # Accept an alert
  agentchrome dialog handle accept

  # Dismiss a confirm dialog
  agentchrome dialog handle dismiss

  # Accept a prompt with text
  agentchrome dialog handle accept \-\-text "my response"
.SH CAPABILITIES
.PP
Browser dialog handling (alert, confirm, prompt, beforeunload)
.TP
.B dialog handle
Accept or dismiss the current browser dialog
.TP
.B action
Action to take: accept or dismiss
.TP
.B --text
Response text for prompt dialogs (only used with 'accept' action)
.TP
.B dialog info
Check whether a dialog is currently open
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Examples:
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog info\`
Check if a dialog is currently open
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle accept\`
Accept an alert or confirm dialog
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle dismiss\`
Dismiss a dialog
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dialog handle accept --text "my input"\`
Accept a prompt dialog with text
